From Olanrewaju Lawal, Birnin Kebbi      Kebbi State Governor, Senator Abubakar Atiku Bagudu and Attorney General of the Federation, Abubakar Chika Malami (SAN), have urged the people of Warra and Ngaski, in Ngaski Local Government Area of the state to vote for Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, presidential candidate of All Progressives Congress (APC) and governorship candidate of the party in the State, Dr. Nasir Idris in the forthcoming general elections. They stated this during the APC campaign in the area, which was attended by former the governor of the state, Alhaji Saidu Nasamu Dakingari and many chieftains of the party. At Ngaski town, a mammoth crowd turned out to watch the eminent personalities campaigning in their domain. While addressing the crowd, Bagudu informed them that President Buhari has anointed Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu as the presidential candidate of the party. He said: “President Muhammadu Buhari asked me to tell you that Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu is his candidate. We should all vote for him. And Dr. Nasir Idris is the governorship candidate of our party in the state. ‘So, I urge all our people in Ngaski and Warra to collect their PVCs, and come out to vote for all the party’s candidates from the governor to Senator, House of Assembly,” he said. In his remarks, Abubakar Chika Malami, told the people of Ngaski town that the main opposition party, PDP, had wasted their 16 years in government without leading the Nigeria to the Promised Land. Malami explained that within seven years of APC, many infrastructure facilities were completed including Sokoto-Koko-Yauri road, 2nd Niger Bridge among others.